 > How does one go about obtaining copies of United States patent descriptions,
 >such as the ones relating to public key cryptography?

  If you have the patent number, it's a simple matter of writing to the
U.S. Patent Office and paying a few bucks for copying and postage.
  Some large libraries also have copies of U.S. patents in their archives.

